Package de.esoco.lib.model

The model package contains a set of interfaces and some base implementations of these that define simple data structures based on the DataModel interface.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Callback<T>
    A callback interface for asynchronous (remote) method executions.
    ColumnDefinition
    The definition of a column in table or tree-table components.
    DataModel<T>
    Interface for data models that represent an indexed set of data elements.
    DataModelListener
    Listener interface for changes in data models.
    DataProvider<T>
    An interface for objects that provide access to indexed data.
    DataSet<T>
    An interface that defines a set of data for charting or similar purposes.
    Downloadable
    An interface for objects (typically DataModels) that allow their content to be downloaded.
    FilterableDataModel<T>
    An extended data model that allows to filter the contained data elements by setting filter constraints for element fields.
    HierarchicalDataModel<T>
    A data model extension for hierarchical data structures.
    MutableDataModel<T>
    A data model extension that allows the modification of data elements.
    ObservableDataModel<T>
    Extended data model interface that allows clients to be notified of changes in the data structure by registering a DataModelListener.
    RemoteDataModel<T>
    An extended data model interface that is optimized for remote access.
    SortableDataModel<T>
    An extended data model that allows to sort the contained data elements by their fields.

Package de.esoco.lib.model Description

The model package contains a set of interfaces and some base implementations of these that define simple data structures based on the DataModel interface. A data model is a iterable structure that provides indexed access to it's data elements.

All classes in this package are safe for use in a limited Java environment like the Javascript translation of GWT.
